## Investigation Complete

**Issue**: #674 - Prod deploy failed on main
**Type**: BUG

### Assessment

| Metric | Value | Reasoning |
|--------|-------|-----------|
| Severity | HIGH | Production deploys failing on every push; no new code can land |
| Complexity | LOW | Single character fix in one file |
| Confidence | HIGH | Error message exactly matches heredoc shell-expansion of `$(seq 1 20)` |

### Root Cause

`$(seq 1 20)` on line 179 of `.github/workflows/staging-pipeline.yml` is inside an unquoted SSH heredoc (`<< EOF`). The local shell expands it to `1\n2\n3\n...20` (with newlines) before sending to the remote host. The remote bash then sees `2` on its own line and throws `syntax error near unexpected token '2'`.

The fix: `$(seq 1 20)` → `\$(seq 1 20)` — identical to how other command substitutions in the same heredoc are correctly escaped (e.g. line 163: `CURRENT_ID=\$(docker inspect ...)`).

